        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down. | Bromley. | Kent. S.E.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Dec 17.</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>Mr Darwin wishes me to write for him as he is too unwell to be able to write himself. He begs me to thank you for your letter &amp; very kind present of the pamphlet.<ref target="#foot.f1"/> I am sorry to say that he has been very unwell for 3 months &amp; though he is making slow progress I am afraid it will be long before he can apply himself to his usual pursuits.</p>
<p>I am with his kind remembrances | yours very truly | Emma Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The reference has not been identified; the pamphlet may have related to CD’s inquiry about <hi rend="italic">Lythrum</hi> (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-4263.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to Alphonse de Candolle, 4 August [1863]</ref>).</note>
        </div>        
            
